In the food and beverage industry, skin packaging has gained significant traction due to its ability to extend the shelf life of perishable goods. Consumers are increasingly looking for convenient and durable packaging solutions that not only preserve the quality of food products but also make them more visually appealing. Skin packaging effectively meets these requirements, making it a preferred choice for companies operating in the food sector. Moreover, the versatility of skin packaging in protecting various types of products during transportation and storage is another factor contributing to its widespread adoption.

